      "decision": "pushed_back",
      "source_file": ".github/workflows/devflow-review.yml",
      "claim_text": "check_suite completion of DevFlow's own posted neutral check re-fires the trigger in a loop",
      "skip_category": "claim-quality",
      "evidence": "create_check POSTs the check with GH_TOKEN (the github-actions app), so the check rides the github-actions app's check suite; GitHub's recursion prevention never delivers check_suite events for Actions-created suites (docs-verified in Phase 2 of the implement run), and the route's CS_APP==github-actions guard is defense in depth. The reviewer itself marked the finding PLAUSIBLE and contingent on exactly this platform behavior"
    },
    {
      "finding_id": "F-9",
      "decision": "pushed_back",
      "source_file": "scripts/derive-review-preconditions.sh",
      "claim_text": "AC11 deviation: zero-visible-runs treated as satisfied at the initial event",
      "skip_category": "claim-quality",
      "evidence": "deliberate, recorded design decision: the issue's prescribed defer-at-initial + completion-re-trigger mechanism cannot exist generically on GitHub (workflow_run needs a named list; check_suite never fires for Actions suites), and defer-at-initial would wedge a CI-less repo forever (AC's own never-wedged requirement). The deviation is recorded in the issue workpad via a 2.2.6 AC rewrite with a --note paper trail and the overclaiming comment was softened this iteration; residual race is cost-bounded, not a correctness hole (the review diffs against current base regardless)"
    },
    {
      "finding_id": "F-16",
      "decision": "pushed_back",
      "source_file": "scripts/derive-review-preconditions.sh",
      "claim_text": "action_required CI runs defer with a generic breadcrumb",
      "skip_category": "claim-quality",
      "evidence": "the deferral breadcrumb already interpolates the specific status/conclusion token ('still <status>' / \"concluded '<conclusion>'\"), so an action_required run is named as such — the suggested wording adds no information"
